news.title: Haryana: Checks on brick kilns soon, those flouting norms to be closed
news.para: The direction comes days after a Supreme Court bench in April passed a slew of directions for the operation of brick kilns in NCR.

news.title: Asian Paints' profit at Rs 874 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations was up 20.60 per cent to Rs 7,889.94 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 6,541.94 crore in the corresponding period of previous fiscal year.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body offers 6% discount to property tax payers
news.para: The civic body has also managed to generate property tax bills for all property owners by Monday. Usually, the bills are generated by the end of May or in the first week of June. The dispatching of bills has also started.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's profit down 6% to Rs 600 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total expenses were at Rs 3,077 crore as against Rs 2,770 crore. However, revenue from operations was up 7.26 per cent to Rs 3,380 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 3,151 crore in the same period a year ago.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 314 buildings without BU permissions
news.para: In an affidavit, the AMC’s town development officer has stated that over the past one year the civic authorities have sealed 277 commercial and 37 residential buildings for want of BU permission.

news.title: Gurugram: 4,000 more shanties demolished along Golf Course Road
news.para: A team, led by district town planner RS Batth, carried out the demolition drive in the presence of over 200 police personnel. Officials said the DTCP will now chalk out a plan to get walls and gates constructed in the residential colony, and also keep a tab on any further illegal construction.

news.title: Delhi government to carry out repairs in vacant EWS flats
news.para: To start with, Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB), which is responsible for identification of eligible slum dwellers through surveys and taking up the allotment process, will be carrying out the repair work of about 2,000 such units located in Dwarka Sector 16.

news.title: Pune: New housing societies can seek deemed conveyance four months after registration
news.para: The move is aimed at helping new housing societies obtain the conveyance deed without further delay, said Kawade, who has issued a directive in this regard.

news.title: Mumbai: 12 years on, 97-year-old gets keys to redeveloped flat
news.para: Though the redeveloped building was ready nearly five years ago, Kamlabai Khamkar was not given a flat in Green Field, Lower Parel, mainly because she had filed complaints against the builder over non-payment of rent in lieu of transit accommodation.

news.title: Housing demand to stay firm in spite of rising prices, interest rates: Crisil
news.para: Affordability, after improving upto 20% between fiscals 2016 and 2021, had started declining from the second half of fiscal 2022.

news.title: Chandigarh: IT Park project to include 15% EWS houses
news.para: The component, one of the key segments of the project coming up at IT Park, was discussed among bidders during the recent pre-bid meeting with CHB’s senior officials.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body to choke business in residential areas, fill coffers
news.para: After a special drive, the GHMC issued notices to around 1,100 buildings across all the six zones. The notice provides a 15-day stipulated period to convert the building from residential to commercial and warns of imposing fines under GHMC Act.

news.title: Realty registrations dip in Kolkata in April as price hike makes buyers cautious
news.para: Real estate analysts said the slowdown in sales and registrations was a reflection of home buyers becoming cautious and postponing the purchase decision due to price hike.

news.title: Government to set up panel on RERA non-compliance
news.para: The government may also seek state governments to provide their inputs in this matter with an objective of making Rera more effective and offering an impactful recourse mechanism to homebuyers. The decision to this effect was taken in the recent meeting of the Central Advisory Council (CAC).

news.title: YEIDA orders forensic audit of Ajnara Panorama, to hire private firm
news.para: Through the audit, officials said, the Authority will get an assessment of the construction completed till now, apart from finding out the exact number of flats sold and possession given to buyers to date.
